      "chunk_in_page": 0,
      "page": 4,
      "slide": null,
      "text": "Recursion Recursive algorithms have recursive descriptions of their runtimes: ● Mergesort makes two recursive calls on arrays of size ≈ n/2 ● The rest of the alg. is Θ(n) We need to solve the recurrence T(n) = 2T(n/2) + Θ(n)."
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": "week3_rectree-510-4",
      "course": "CSC510",
      "source_file": "week3_rectree-510.pdf",
      "chunk_index": 4,
      "chunk_in_page": 0,
      "page": 5,
      "slide": null,
      "text": "Recursion Substitution is kind of hard to understand… T(n) = 2T(n/2) + cn"
    },
    {
